  "prompt": "Why do I get snapchat notifications of some people but not others?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why you might receive Snapchat notifications for some contacts but not others:\n\n1. Notification settings\n- You may have customized notification settings for specific friends\n- Some contacts might be muted or have reduced notification preferences\n\n2. Interaction frequency\n- Snapchat prioritizes notifications from people you interact with more often\n- Friends you snap or chat with regularly are more likely to trigger notifications\n\n3. Snapstreaks\n- Active Snapstreaks might increase notification frequency\n- Maintaining daily communication can lead to more frequent alerts\n\n4. Privacy settings\n- Some friends might have adjusted their privacy settings\n- They could limit who can send them snaps or see their content\n\n5. App settings\n- Your Snapchat app settings might affect notification behavior\n- Check your notification preferences in the app settings\n\n6. Device settings\n- Your phone's notification settings can impact Snapchat alerts\n- Ensure Snapchat has permission to send notifications\n\n7. Account status\n- Inactive or deleted accounts might not send notifications\n- Account restrictions could affect notification delivery\n\nTo resolve inconsistent notifications, check your Snapchat and device settings, and ensure you have the latest app version.",
